John H. Gibson II of Texas has been nominated to be the Chief Management Officer at the Department of Defense. Currently serving as the Deputy Chief Management Officer, Mr. Gibson has a background in aerospace and finance. He was previously the President and CEO of XCOR Aerospace, Inc., as well as holding leadership positions with Beechcraft. Mr. Gibson has also served in various government roles, including Assistant Secretary of the Air Force and Deputy Under Secretary of Defense. He holds degrees in economics and finance, and has received the Air Force Award for Exceptional Civilian Service.